(1) Career and technical
education means educational programs that support the development of knowledge
and skill in the following areas: Agriculture, food, and natural resources;
architecture and construction; arts, audiovisual, technology, and communication;
business management and administration; education and training; finance; government
and public administration; health science; hospitality and tourism; human
services; information technology; law, public safety, and security; marketing;
manufacturing; science, technology, engineering, and mathematics; and transportation,
distribution, and logistics;
